definition:
μιαίνω 
 [in LXX chiefly for טָמֵא ;] 
  1. to dye or stain. 
   2. to stain, defile, soil; 
   (a) in physical sense; 
   (b) in moral sense : Tit.1:15, Heb.12:15, Ju 8; 
   (with) in ritual sense (cf. Lev.22:5, al.): Jhn.18:28.†
 SYN.: μολύνω, to besmear, which also differs from μ. in that it is never used, as μ. in its primary meaning, in an honourable sense (cf. Tr., Syn., § xxxi)  (AS)
